---

<div>
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <span class="eyebrow">Outcomes</span>
    <h2 class="mt-5 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
      What DEVS trains you to do
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg copy-muted max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      Not course completion badges. The specific capabilities that make a team want to work with you.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="surface-card p-8">
      <p class="text-base copy-muted mb-6">
        I can pick up a ticket, branch, build, open a PR, and respond to review feedback without hand-holding.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <p class="text-xs copy-subtle font-mono">Outcome: End-to-end delivery confidence</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="surface-card p-8">
      <p class="text-base copy-muted mb-6">
        I can explain why I made a technical decision, what I'd change, and what I learned — not just what framework I used.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <p class="text-xs copy-subtle font-mono">Outcome: Interview-ready engineering stories</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="surface-card p-8">
      <p class="text-base copy-muted mb-6">
        I communicate blockers early, write clear standup updates, and give useful review feedback — not just code.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <p class="text-xs copy-subtle font-mono">Outcome: Team communication that earns trust</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
